The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Sourav Ganguly and film-maker Sandip Ray will attend the foundation stone laying ceremony of an Eastern Railway stadium in Behala on Thursday, said railway minister Mamata Banerjee on Monday. The stadium will be named after Satyajit Ray. I am happy that both Ganguly and Ray today confirmed their presence at the ceremony, the railway minister said.   he ministry has allocated Rs 56 crore for the proposed stadium, she added. The stadium will have a seating capacity of about 20,000.     A 24-year-old man was found hanging from the ceiling of a rice godown on Rabindra Sarani early on Monday. Sanjoy Saha, a resident of Kripanath Lane in Shyampukur area, was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared dead.    The state coordination committee will hand over a cheque for Rs 1 crore to chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee at Writers Buildings on October 14 for the rehabilitation of villagers affected by cyclone Aila, Ananta Bandyopadhyay, the general secretary of the committee, said on Monday.                                                                                                                                                                
